Closure Details: MATCH CLOSURE SUMMARY Describe the reasons for closure and any extenuating circumstances: As noted in recent MSC's, the reason this match is closing is complex and difficult to summarize concisely. There is conflicting information from both sides but nothing warranting further investigation. Child safety specialist was consulted during the closure process and concurred no major violation occurred that would warrant a CPS report. Essentially, PG and LS claim that issues with BS' "character" and personality had a persistent and negative effect on the match and culminated during their final meeting at the zoo. PG and LS failed to report any of these issues, nor their seriousness, in any MSC's going back over 18 months. PG and LS claim BS is controlling, judgmental, and unwilling to accommodate LS' needs related to her mental health. PG said that they never developed a strong bond. Again, previous MSC's from all parties directly or implicitly refute nearly all of these claims. The "breaking point" occurred when LS desired to go home during their most recent meetup, citing her discomfort with being around BS' family that made her feel left out. PG and LS accuse BS of ignoring LS' request and ignoring PG's outreach over the phone during this meetup. BS' statement contradicts this account and shows that PG and BS were in contact during the meetup and that BS was actively trying to find a solution to an issue that has been persistent in their relationship. LS would experience mood swings, possibly related to her bipolar disorder/social anxiety, and BS had been asking for support on how best to handle this for several months, or longer. BS said that she and PG had several conversations about how to choose when to accommodate LS when she wants to leave or quit something vs. encouraging her to "push through" and stick with something. PG and LS had no desire to work through this issue and requested immediate closure with no contact from BS. I agreed to do so. It is difficult to accurately assign responsibility for why this match has fallen apart. BS clearly violated the BBBS guideline of 1-1 meetups but was willing to take accountability for this. BS also admitted on several occassions that she was struggling to support LS as she was experiencing symptoms of very serious mental health disorders. BS was willing to accept coaching from BBBS and PG and there is ample evidence that she had requested this from both parties. I have found several examples of BS requesting resources from BBBS and advocating for LS. She was more communicative and engaged with BBBS than most Bigs. On the other hand, PG and LS repeatedly violated the 1-1 guideline as well. The major difference being that they seemed to actively withhold this information from BBBS during MSC's. BS reported that their families had multiple interactions with each other and she never received any negative feedback about this from PG or LS. Considering the gravity of the character flaws and behavior PG and LS described during their last MSC, it's difficult to comprehend how almost nothing was mentioned during the 3.5 years leading up to closure. To conclude, I agree that closure is the best way forward for everyone invollved. PG cited that she is still grateful for BBBS and the match. She said that it essentially boiled down to clash of personalities and a lack of a deep bond. BS is shocked and remorseful. I was surprised, based on the picture painted by PG and LS, that BS was so receptive to their feedback about her behavior. BS took accountability and apologized. I will not encourage BS to reenroll, but I will not discourage her if she shows interest and advocates for herself. Closure Details: This was a difficult match from the beginning, at least for the Bs. She felt I believe that ls had different expectations of the match, and was somewhat difficult to engage. Then Bs became pregnant and continued to vacillate between planning to keep the match open and not. I told her to give herself lots of time, before and after the baby was born. After several months I tried to connect with her. Finally I was able to email with her,and she told me she was moving, there was a death in the family I believe, all around the time the baby was to be born. Again I was unable to contact her, or really engage her in deciding what to do. I did try to give her lots of space and advice, particularly when she told me she had postpartum depression. Finally, after not hearing from the aunt/foster parent to any extent, I wrote letters saying that I would have to close if I was unable to talk to either of them. Then I got the email from Bs, and I wrote to her that she did a fine job in sending a letter. (I had encouraged her to do this if she didn't have the energy to see or talk to Ls. Aunt was aware I think of difficulties Bs was having. I have not heard from the aunt/foster mother. I will close the match. There was no closing meeting ,but Bs did a great job with her letter, as I had encouraged her to do. I would not rematch this Bs unless she feels she is able to handle being a big, and is over the depression. As to ls, this is a very needy child, who has had a lot of bad experiences in her life, but I think she was not particularly receptive to, at least this, big sister. I would recommend seeing where ls is at, and she and her aunt's view of this match and closing.

She always said they wen to actiities where there were other kids there.. such as activities at a Fire Station where she knew people. Lb said that Bs was always correcting his speech. In the initial notes, it was noted by the matching worker that Bs did this at the match meeting,although it was not seen as mean spirited, it did seem a tad out of place at a first meeting. Grandmother had lots of complaints about Bs, and Bs said that grandmother never seemed to know her name, and was rude to her. I really tried to encourage the match, but I just think they did not get along. Lb seems to be a nice kid, and honestly just wants someone to do things with.. He said a female again would be okay if she were nice,but he really wants a male. Lb and Grandmother both say they want Lb to be rematched. I have to say that Bs seemed quite enthusiastic about the match, and I did have to frequently encourage her to call and make plans for the match I would not recommend Bs to be rematched. I would like to see Lb to get another chance at being matched..he seems sincere in this and pretty open and eager. There were no safety issues that I was aware of.

Closure Details: The match was going very well at the beginning. After being matched for 4 months, Little attended Big's home, as they were planning to cook dinner/bake. Little met Big's significant other and felt that she wasn't welcome into the home, as the SO did not speak to her. Mom addressed this with MEC and stated that she didn't know that Big has a SO and isn't too pleased about it. MEC coached Mom that bigs are allowed to be free in their social life and BBBS doesn't reject volunteers who have a relationship outside of BBBS. Mom was understanding but still had some hesitation. The match continued for another month, but Mom called back and shared that Little has stated that she wanted the match closed. MEC spoke with Little and Little shared that she feels unsafe and uncomfortable with Big Sister. When MEC asked why, she shared that after the last activity, she just doesn't feel comfortable with Big anymore. MEC asked if anything else happened during Big's place, and Little stated that nothing happened, she wasn't left alone, and Big was good to her, but she didn't like feeling unwelcome by Big's SO. MEC tried coaching Little that Big has a personal life, which she said she understands, but she doesn't like feeling "unwelcome". MEC couldn't proceed forward coaching Little, as Little started shutting down. MEC thanked Little and spoke with Mom. Mom shared that she wants her child to feel safe and welcome. Mom was adamant and would like the match closed. MEC spoke with Big Sister and asked about the activity taken at her location, and she shared that it went well. She said they made pizza and watched "turning red". MEC asked if Little was left alone at all during her time at Big's place, to which Big said "no". MEC also asked about Big's SO, which Big stated that he was there but he was in their room the majority of the time because he didn't want to conflict with their activity. MEC probe SO interacts with Little, to which Big said no. MEC shared that Little felt uncomfortable when she was at Big's place because of the SO. Big didn't have any idea, as the SO wasn't around them the majority of the time. When MEC shared that both Mom/Little would like the match closed, Big was taken back quite a bit. Big shared that she is unsure why Little would like the match closed as they were doing so well together but she also shared that she respects Little's decision as she also wants Little to feel comfortable and safe. Based on the information, MEC conclude the match is closed due to incompatibility. It looks like both Mom/Little would like a Big that isn't in a relationship, as Big may/may not be living with their SO, this can make Little feel uncomfortable when doing activities at Big's location.
